findings.lower_chest: A 2-3 mm nodule is seen in the right lung base. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion.
findings.hepatobiliary: A couple subcentimeter hypodensities in the right hepatic lobe, likely hepatic cysts or biliary hamartomas. Liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation with no focal lesions or biliary dilatation.
findings.pancreas: Normal attenuation throughout. Abnormal dilatation of the main pancreatic duct, measuring up to 5 mm.
findings.spleen: Small subcentimeter hypodensity possibly a small hemangioma. Normal size and attenuation otherwise.
findings.urinary: Normal and symmetric kidneys with normal nephrogram. Multiple cortically based hypodense lesions, most small, largest measuring up to 1.3 cm compatible with simple cysts.
findings.gastrointestinal: Enlarged appendix measuring up to 2.0 cm with adjacent fat stranding; a tiny pocket of rim enhancing fluid adjacent to the appendix. Mild thickening of the distal terminal ileum.
findings.pelvis: Urinary bladder and distal ureters unremarkable. No free fluid.
findings.vascular: No abdominal aortic aneurysm. Mild atherosclerotic disease noted.
findings.bones: No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture. Sclerotic focus in L5 vertebral body likely represents bone island.
findings.soft_tissues: Tiny fat containing umbilical hernia. Abdominal and pelvic wall within normal limits.
